      ],
      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(signal: 1D numeric array (time-series amplitude), rest: numeric scalar (baseline/rest amplitude reference), sampling_rate: positive numeric scalar (Hz), threshold: positive numeric scalar (detection threshold multiplier or absolute level), active_state_duration: positive numeric scalar (minimum duration in seconds for a valid active state)) -> array of integer sample indices marking detected onset events",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "primitive_binding_confidence": 0.0,
      "primitive_binding_source": "",
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "threshold_hysteresis_state_transition_onset_detector. Scans a 1D scalar time-series for transitions from a low-energy quiescent state to a sustained high-energy active state by evaluating whether the signal amplitude exceeds a scaled or absolute threshold derived from a baseline reference value. A candidate transition is confirmed only when the above-threshold condition persists continuously for a minimum duration window (expressed in samples via the sampling rate), enforcing temporal hysteresis and suppressing transient noise spikes. The output is a monotonically increasing sparse index set marking the precise sample positions where each confirmed state transition originates.. Applications: Seismology \u2014 detecting the onset of seismic P-wave or S-wave arrivals in a continuous ground-motion amplitude trace by identifying when vibration energy exceeds a baseline noise floor for a minimum sustained window, marking rupture initiation times, Neuroscience \u2014 identifying action potential burst onsets in extracellular electrode recordings by detecting when local field potential amplitude transitions from resting membrane noise into sustained above-threshold depolarization, used for spike-train analysis, Industrial condition monitoring \u2014 locating the precise start of mechanical vibration events (e.g., gear tooth contact, bearing fault impulses) in accelerometer time-series by comparing instantaneous envelope amplitude against a quiescent idle-state reference over a minimum engagement duration, Acoustics and speech processing \u2014 segmenting audio streams into voiced/unvoiced regions by detecting transitions from silence (near-zero energy baseline) to sustained phonation, enabling automatic utterance boundary detection in raw waveform data",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
